{
  "texts": [
    "[19] adopt a slightly different approach and propose a visual MPC controller that outputs a sequence of velocity commands based on the current image and a trajectory of subgoal images.",
    "Authors in [20] regress depth images and actions to collision probabilities which is then minimized within an MPC framework.",
    "Although theoretically, this approach can be extended to work with estimated depth, it is unclear how the associated noise will affect the efficiency of the overall pipeline.",
    "Moreover, we believe that predicting obstacle clearance distribution is easier than directly predicting collision probabilities, as the supervision data for the former can be easily obtained.",
    "Our design choice also allows us to use sophisticated statistical tools to capture collision risk from the clearance samples in an efficient manner."
  ]
}